You are implementing a logistics shipment tracking Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-3cc88d1e16ac41909bb03de81021cca6/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

## Project Structure
- **Server project**: `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/` — hosts the app, has EF Core with SQLite, ASP.NET Identity
- **Client project**: `ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/` — WebAssembly components
- This is **Auto Global** mode: all interactive components go in the `.Client` project. No `@rendermode` needed on pages.
- Data access from interactive components must go through HTTP APIs (not direct DbContext).

## What to implement

### 1. Shared Models (in `.Client` project, since both sides need them)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id);
    Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Client-side service implementation (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs` — uses `HttpClient` to call API:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        var response = await http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/{id}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>())!;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 4. Register HttpClient and service in Client `Program.cs`

Update `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs` to add:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddHttpClient("ServerAPI", client =>
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress))
    .AddHttpMessageHandler<CookieHandler>();
builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => sp.GetRequiredService<IHttpClientFactory>().CreateClient("ServerAPI"));
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

Wait — actually for WASM in Auto mode, the auth cookie is sent automatically. We don't need a special cookie handler. Just use a simple HttpClient:

```csharp
